1. That the complainants are consumers of the opposite party Development Authority.

2. That upon application by the complainants in the prescribed form with the prescribed fee,
the opposite party department allotted plots on a lottery basis in the L.I.G First colonies located in Ward-8, Kanpur Nagar. 
Upon their names being drawn in the lottery, the opposite party made the allotment, 
in which complainant number 1 was allotted house number D-225 LIG First located in Ward-8, Kanpur Nagar, 
complainant number 2 was allotted building number D-409 LIG First located in Ward-8, Kanpur Nagar, 
complainant number 4 was allotted building number D-430 LIG First located in Bara, Kanpur Nagar, 
complainant number 3 was allotted building number D-530 LIG First located in Bara, Kanpur Nagar,
complainant number 5 was allotted building number H-335 LIG First located in Bara, Kanpur Nagar, 
complainant number 6 was allotted building number H-336 LIG First located in Bara, Kanpur Nagar, 
and complainant number 7 was allotted building number C-127 LIG First located in Bara, Kanpur Nagar.

3. That the The complainants have been paying the required amount and monthly installments to the opposite party as stipulated. 
Photocopies of all the receipts are being submitted along with this complaint letter.

4. That in the past month, when all the complainants went to the office of the opposing department to obtain information regarding the 
total amount of installments for their respective properties,

page 24

they were informed that they would have to deposit the entire amount of their installments or arrange for the 
necessary funds to complete the registration of their properties. The concerned clerk/employee then informed them that 
they would now have to deposit at the rate of Rs. 1600/- per square meter, otherwise their building allotment would be canceled.

5. illegible

6. That the complainants are ready to deposit the amount with the opposing department, 
along with late payment charges and interest, as per the agreement made at the time of applying for the plot.
However, the opposing department is demanding payment at the rate of Rs. 1600/- per square meter, which is excessively high, 
and the opposing department has no right to determine the rate in such an arbitrary manner.

7. That the complainants are ready to deposit the amount with the opposing department, 
along with interest, as per the terms and conditions of the agreement at the time of allotment of their respective houses, while the opposing department

Page 25

is demanding the alleged cost of the house at the rate of Rs. 1600/- per square meter, 
and is threatening to cancel the application if the amount is not deposited at the rate of Rs. 1600/-. 
The opposite party/department has no authourity to do so.

8. That this Honorable Forum has full jurisdiction to hear and decide this complaint.

Prayer

The complainants pray as follows:

a. That to order opposite party be directed to allot the house only according to the agreement made at the time of allotment.

b. That to issue an order directing the opposing party not to take any action to cancel the proposed allocation based on the deposit of funds through a complaint.

c. illegible

d. That any relief be granted in favor of the appropriate council against the opposing party.

