|2|
Additional Statement

7. That the complainants numbered 1 to 7 were allotted houses for the economically
weaker section by the opposite party, but the complainants have been negligent
in depositing the installments for the allotted houses as per the agreement,
for which notices were sent by the opposite party on dated such as 11-7-96, 21-8-01,
23-1-2002 through registered post.

8. That, in addition, the opposite party sent a letter to all the complainants under the One-Time Settlement Scheme 
issued by the Uttar Pradesh Government on 21-08-2001, but the complainants paid no attention to it and did not deposit 
any money for the said houses. Despite repeated notices, when the complainants did not deposit the money for the houses in question, 
the Vice-Chairman of the opposite party authority, through his order dated 07-01-2002, canceled the allotment of the houses in favor of the complainants.

9. That the information regarding the said cancellation was also sent to the complainants by the opposite party through registered post.  
Meanwhile, the complainants requested the restoration of the houses after the cancellation, which the opposite party, adopting a humane approach, 
revoked the cancellation order and directed them to deposit the money. 
However, the complainants still did not deposit a single penny and filed a complaint in the Hon'ble Forum.

10. That the complainants' complaint is contrary to the above facts and is liable to be dismissed.

11. That the complaint is contrary to the definition and objectives of the Consumer Protection Act and is liable to be rejected.

12. That no cause of action has arisen for filing the complaint, nor is the complainants' complaint prima facie proven. 
Nor does the balance of convenience favor the complainants.

13. That the complainants are not entitled to any of the reliefs sought in the complaint. 
The opposite party has not committed any deficiency in providing services to the complainants.

14. That on the basis of the above grounds, it is necessary in the interest of justice that the objection of the opposite party be accepted 
and the complaint filed by the complainants be summarily dismissed. 

15. That the complaint filed by the complainants is filed with the intention of wasting the defendant's money and time, and 



Page 29

it is not just should therefore be dismissed and cancelled.
Opponent
